<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-10-09T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-10-09T21:00:00-05:00" n="259" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d259">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.77/1633</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Reinsch</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-10-10T10:00:00+08:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 10, 1917, 10
                                a.m</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>My telegram August 9, 10 a.m. Please inform whether the British
                            Government has expressed itself further concerning the protest which is
                            now delaying the construction of the American railway in Hunan, Hupeh,
                            the survey having been completed.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>